    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nMany function docstrings, particularly in Lua, use code examples of the form:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n--- Example:\r\n--- <pre>lua\r\n--- local x = vim.foo.bar()\r\n--- </pre>\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, these can become outdated or contain errors.\r\n\r\n### Proposal\r\n\r\nA useful feature would be to run these samples automatically in CI to validate them (make sure they actually run). If we can decide on a format, we could even run them and validate their output. For example, one format we could use is:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n--- <pre>lua\r\n--- some_function()\r\n--- -- expected output when printing\r\n--- </pre>\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome script in CI would see this snippet in the docstring, run `some_function()` and verify that its output is `expected output when printing`.\r\n\r\nThis is not always possible of course, and may not be sophisticated enough to cover all cases, but hopefully it communicates the concept.",
